                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre but careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        The scribe ʾalaqā  <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12932TawaldaHesan">Tawalda Ḥǝḍān </persName> is mentioned in Additio
                        1 (the note adds also what can be his baptismal or his father's name Gabra
                           Śǝllāse).<date>Late 19th - early 20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist; names of the
                           donors and scribes; groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I and
                           II; incipit of Text III; incipits of sections and miracles; names of the
                           months; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#4v">Fol. 4v: </locus>
                        <desc>The commissioner (däğğazmač <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4997hagosTa">Ḥāgʷas
                           Tafari</persName>).</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#5r">Fol. 5r: </locus>
                        <desc>The Virgin Mary with her Child.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#72v">Fol. 72v: </locus>
                        <desc>St. Gabra Manfas Qǝddus.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#73r">Fol. 73r: </locus>
                        <desc>The wife of the donor (with their daughter?).</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#70rb">ff. 70rb</locus>
                           <desc>-va, 72rb: Note on commissioning of the writing, extended by the
                              list of the commissioner's family members (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note mentions the commissioner, “the governor of Tǝgray”
                              (tǝgre makʷanni) Ḥāgʷas ( <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4997hagosTa"><addName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</addName> Ḥāgʷas
                                 Tafari</persName>), whose baptismal
                              name is Zawalda Māryām. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Chains of black and red dots in some fols.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
