               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0042MR">Mǝdra Rubā Sǝllase</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1870" notAfter="1920">Late 19th - early 20th
                        century</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Commissioned by “the governor of Tǝgray”
                     (Tǝgre makʷannǝn ) Ḥāgʷas (daǧǧāzmāč <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4997hagosTa">Ḥāgʷas
                     Tafari</persName>) “whose baptismal name is Zawalda Māryām". Members of his family are
                     also mentioned: his wife Walatta Madḫǝn, his son and daughter (s. supplication
                     formulas, e.g., <locus target="#10va">10va</locus>, esp. Additio 1, <locus target="#70rb">70rb-</locus>va). Other names (qaññāzmāč <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3399DastaSe">Dastā</persName> etc.),
                     apparently also of Ḥāgʷas’s relatives, are mentioned; further names of persons
                     probably belonging to the same family are mentioned on <locus target="#72rb">72rb</locus>.</provenance>
               </history>
